TITLE: Example Page Object Model in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates a basic Page Object Model implementation for a login page, encapsulating element selectors and login actions.

SOURCE: https://github.com/davila7/claude-code-templates/blob/main/cli-tool/components/commands/testing/e2e-setup.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
class LoginPage {
  constructor(page) {
    this.page = page;
    this.emailInput = page.locator('#email');
    this.passwordInput = page.locator('#password');
    this.loginButton = page.locator('#login-btn');
  }

  async login(email, password) {
    await this.emailInput.fill(email);
    await this.passwordInput.fill(password);
    await this.loginButton.click();
  }
}
```

