TITLE: Technical Implementation Example (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: A real-world JavaScript example demonstrating class implementation with configuration, task execution, and error handling.

SOURCE: https://github.com/davila7/claude-code-templates/blob/main/cli-tool/components/agents/expert-advisors/agent-expert.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Real-world example with comments
class ExampleImplementation {
  constructor(options) {
    this.config = {
      // Default configuration
      timeout: options.timeout || 5000,
      retries: options.retries || 3
    };
  }

  async performTask(data) {
    try {
      // Implementation logic with error handling
      const result = await this.processData(data);
      return this.formatResponse(result);
    } catch (error) {
      throw new Error(`Task failed: ${error.message}`);
    }
  }
}
```

